-- Ex-Alcatel exec pleads guilty in Costa Rica bribes
-- 
-- Thu Jun 7, 2007 7:01pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/07/us-alcatel-costarica-idUSWEN866320070607

 

 SAN FRANCISCO  (Reuters) - A former executive of Alcatel has pleaded guilty to taking part in a scheme to give more than $2.5 million in bribes to Costa Rican government officials for a mobile phone contract, the U.S. Department of Justice said on Thursday. 

 Christian Sapsizian faces up to 10 years in prison and fines. Alcatel is now part of Alcatel-Lucent ALU.PA.